{"lemma":"تارِيخٌ","slug":"تارِيخٌ","root":"#.ر.خ","root_slug":"_-ر-خ","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ر-خ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n558"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AE%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of أَرَّخَ (ʔarraḵa) (form II)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"synonym of تَارِيخ (tārīḵ, “date; history”)","tags":["nonstandard"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of أَرَّخَ (ʔarraḵa, “to date, to write the date”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n558","headword_ar":"تَاْرِيخٌ","root":"Arx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 2. ―         -b2-  Also, [as a subst., generally pronounced without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A date; an era; an epoch;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uroxapN","text_ar":"اُرْخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a subst. [signifying the same,] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araxa","text_ar":"اَرَخَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^oriyxu Alhijorapi","text_ar":"تَاْرِيخُ الهِجْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The era,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"epoch, of the Emigration"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Flight"},{"kind":"text","text":"(for such it really was)] of Mohammad [from Mekkeh to El-Medeeneh], (L, Msb,) which his companions, in the time of 'Omar, agreed to make their era, commencing the year from the first appearance of the new moon of [the month] ElMoharram, [two months before the Flight itself,] and making the day to commence from sunset: (Msb:) it is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^oriyxa Almusolimiyna","text_ar":"تَاْرِيخَ المُسْلِمِينَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the era,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"epoch, of the Muslims."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utmost limit, term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything: whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN taA^oriyxu quwomihi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ تَاْرِيخُ قُوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the person from whom date the nobility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminence, and dominion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"authority, of his people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Es- Soolee, Mgh, TA.) ―         -b4-  [Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chronicle; a book of annals; a history:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawaAriyxu","text_ar":"تَوَارِيخُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taworiyxN","text_ar":"تَوْرِيخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["L","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}